There is this thing someone told me about barbell squats where the closer you are to your max, the better your form gets. When it's heavy and dangerous you automatonically do it in the most efficient way. Oldheads tell kids with bad form to squat lighter, but it's not good advice

It reminds me of how parents often complain their kid can't do anything right, can't cook an egg, wash dishes, etc., but kids just like that often end up doing insane shit like surviving a week in open wilderness eating nuts and sleeping in the cold when they get lost in a forest

A trained adult would likely die in such circumstances! But the "spoiled" kid survives! Urgency and raw reality reveal the truth. When DEATH is on the table, you rise up to the occasion to meet your fate. Also this is a Missing 411 David Paulides post disguised as a normie thread
